2. Underlying source materials — original terms apply
-----------------------------------------------------
The underlying source materials (item 2 above) remain governed by their own
licenses and legal status, NOT by CC BY 4.0:

  - Korean statutes, rules, and official notices fall under the non-protected
    categories described in Article 7 of the Korean Copyright Act
    (저작권법 제7조) and are not subject to copyright.
  - Public-data entries are governed by their Public Data Portal license terms
    (e.g. Korea Open Government License / 이용허락범위), as recorded per source
    in data/source_manifest.jsonl.
  - Announcement documents (PDF/HWP/HWPX) are the property of their issuing
    institutions and are NOT redistributed here.

Do NOT redistribute raw third-party source documents unless their individual
license clearly permits it. To reconstruct the corpus for evaluation, fetch the
sources yourself from the official URLs (see docs/public_reconstruction.md).


Disclaimer
----------
This benchmark is for model evaluation and research only. It must not be used to
provide legal, financial, or housing-eligibility advice to real applicants.
